h1. ui:message

h2. Purpose

This tag renders a message for the user, such as an info or warning message.

See also [ui:displayMessage|Tags UI] for the variant that renders the message set by the controller.

h2. Example

{code:xml}
<ui:message type="warning" text="alert.message.something.dodgy"/>
<ui:message type="info">This is some my inline message</ui:message>
{code}

h2. Attributes

{table}
*Name* | *Required?* | *Description*
type |  | The type of the message. Valid values are 'info', 'error', 'warning' and 'debug'. 'debug' messages are only shown in the DEVELOPMENT environment.
text |  | If specified, will be used as the text content for the cell, translated using i18n message bundle if found. If not specified, the body will be used.
textArgs |  | Used as the arguments for the "text" i18n message if used.
{table}